scripts.name: ScrollScript
scripts.rawScript:
end
:touch
play "gfdg#f#d#agea#g#f-gfdg#f#d#agea#g#f-gfdg#f#d#agea#g#f"
scroll bold "Welcome, Adventurer!"
scroll "Your quest begins here, in the strangely low-resolution Village of JZT."
scroll "Your task is to locate the five purple keys hidden throughout this mysterious village. These keys will unlock the five purple doors leading to the Hidden  Palace of JZT. This palace is said to contain untold wealth as a reward for deserving adventurers, and you just might be up to the task!"
scroll "Getting to the palace will not be easy, however. An ancient scroll known only as CodePage 437 warns that ferocious creatures and intricate puzzles stand in the way to whomever dares seek the treasure."
scroll "There are a few things you need to know before embarking on such a dangerous journey..."
scroll bold "Your Health"
scroll "You begin your quest with a paltry 50 health points, which will be reduced by 10 each time you're injured. Once you reach zero health points, I'm afraid it's curtains for you and your adventure!"
scroll "Luckily, you can recover health points by collecting gems (1 point each), up to your maximum. There are also several hearts hidden throughout the village which will increase your maximum health by 10 points each--if you're lucky enough to find them!"
scroll bold "Defending Yourself"
scroll "To survive in this land of uncertainty, you're going to need a weapon. Luckily you've got your trusty zapper by your side! Less luckily, it seems, your zapper needs ammunition, and you're going to have to find it."
scroll "Once you've got some ammo, though, you can shoot by holding down the SPACE key and pressing an ARROW key in the direction you want to shoot. Easy, right?"
scroll bold "Saving Your Game"
scroll "Of course, you should expect to meet an unfortunate demise when embarking on such a perilous journey. To avoid having to restart from the beginning, it would be wise to save your game regularly."
scroll "Save your game by pressing the [S] key at any time during your adventure. It is strongly recommended to keep several save points throughout your journey. It's possible to find yourself stuck and unable to continue, so saving often may be your only chance for success!"
scroll bold "The Purple Keys"
scroll "Keys in the land of JZT are enchanted (for some reason), allowing you to only carry one of each color at a time. This means that once you find a purple key, you need to bring it immediately to the palace to unlock a purple door. Once you get into the palace, you're quest will be nearly over."
scroll bold "More help..."
scroll "If you need more help, please feel free to consult the gameplay manual or support forums on the JZT website at any time."
scroll bold "Best of luck, adventurer!"
scroll bold "You'll need it!"
end

tiles.text: Lions generally move around haphazardly, but some are more intelligent than others.
Tigers, as we all know, act very much like lions do, but also carry guns.

Bears like to hibernate, but will charge toward you if you find yourself aligned with them.
Fun Fact: Bears will tear down breakable walls if they're in the way, but then will immediately die of exhaustion.
Ruffians dart about erratically, charging at their prey with bursts of speed.
Snakes... don't seem to do much, do they?

Centipedes, naturally, crawl about and take several shots to defeat.
Fun Fact: If you split a centipede in two, it becomes two centipedes. We at the zoo recently found this out, which is why there are two here today.
